<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 01 at 3:58PM EDT  by NWS Jacksonville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Pierce
and southeastern Bacon Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Alma, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, half inch hail, and minor flooding
due to heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Minor flooding due to heavy rainfall is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Alma, Jamestown, Bristol and New Lacy.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
